{"id": "EUVD-2024-44790", "enisaUuid": "79e965dc-79fb-3d2e-b9ab-c6d860099569", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmedia: vivid: fix buffer overwrite when using > 32 buffers\n\nThe maximum number of buffers that can be requested was increased to\n64 for the video capture queue. But video capture used a must_blank\narray that was still sized for 32 (VIDEO_MAX_FRAME). This caused an\nout-of-bounds write when using buffer indices >= 32.\n\nCreate a new define MAX_VID_CAP_BUFFERS that is used to access the\nmust_blank array and set max_num_buffers for the video capture queue.\n\nThis solves a crash reported by:\n\n\thttps://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=219258", "datePublished": "2024-11-19T01:30:32", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:21", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e6bacd8f2178b22859fe6d9f755f19dfcd9d3862", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/96d8569563916fe2f8fe17317e20e43f54f9ba4b"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50288"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2af97246-3060-30d9-a744-6aaca558285f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "406b18eb-3ae3-3a4b-9c5d-ad7ed86c23dd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "cea70ed416b428f8214be196d62cc7ffaa11f1b8 <96d8569563916fe2f8fe17317e20e43f54f9ba4b"}, {"id": "5754df42-104c-3183-a20b-e611d84daf06", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.8"}, {"id": "7ef8f44d-a827-3d46-8d4f-0571bd1ded82", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.8"}, {"id": "a22cd37d-42fb-3c6d-8693-97417ef9bb53", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "faf73d91-64bb-3138-b8fa-18aff5ba66b8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "cea70ed416b428f8214be196d62cc7ffaa11f1b8 <e6bacd8f2178b22859fe6d9f755f19dfcd9d3862"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "e